title: For Sale:  Romanian AKM-47 (7.62x39mm)
postcontent:
ITEM DESCRIPTION:SALE only - no trades, please.
 
Romanian AK-47 made by CN Romarm SA/Cugir. Imported by Century Arms into the US. 
Lightly used, in great shape. standard wood furniture. palm-swell-finger-groove pistol grip. 30-rd steel magazine. 
According to research, there were two Arsenals manufacturing the AKM rifle in Romania: Cugir and SADAR. Unlike Arsenal SADAR, which always produced weapons sold as contract arms to other countries and other militant groups, Arsenal Cugir was the sole producer of arms used by the Romanian military. Arsenal Cugir no longer produces small arms, so modern Romanian WASRs are all SADAR-built. If WASR AKMs received something of a bad reputation, it was due to the lower quality of the SADAR rifles, slapped together for foreign sale. It was rumored that in the 90's, the Romanians would actually use Cugir-built guns as "demos" to make sales, but the rifles that shipped were actually SADAR-built. 
Additional WASR info found online here:   http : // www . akfiles . com / forums / showthread.php?p= 194767# post 194767 (paste to browser and remove all spaces)

title: For Sale:  New CZ  P07 Duty
postcontent: Don’t let the “Duty” designation trick you. The P-07 model is a compact handgun — just as appropriate for concealed carry as it is for uniformed duty. The abbreviated 3.8” barrel and compact grip allow the Duty to easily disappear under clothing. This compact size and polymer frame along with the new slide profile (fully machined from bar stock) reduce weight, making the P-07 Duty a great choice for concealed carry. The absence of the grips resulted in some available space that was used to increase the magazine capacity to 12 rounds of 40 S&W. The most innovative feature of the P-07 duty is the Omega trigger system. It simplifies the CZ 75 trigger system, using fewer parts and improves the trigger pull, but the real story is in the versatility it provides its owner. The Omega system allows users to choose between operating the handgun with a decocking lever (installed) or a manual safety (included) by a simple parts change. Additionally, the magazine release can be easily changed from right hand to left hand orientation

The Specialist is one of the newest additions to the Dan Wesson stable. When police departments approached us to build them a more reliable, durable 1911 to replace the ones they had been carrying, we developed a model just for them. The additions that made it ideal for law enforcement also make it perfect for home defense, so we gladly offer it for sale to the public.
A full-size 1911, the Specialist is chambered in .45 or 9mm and loaded with features to satisfy a public servant’s special requirements. The forged stainless steel slide wears our popular Clark-style serrated rib with a single amber tritium dot in the rear sight and a green lamp with white target ring in front.

Equipped with an ambidextrous thumb safety, extended magazine release and detachable two-piece magwell, the Specialist is operator-friendly. It is finished off with a set of G10 VZ Operator II grips that force the hand into the beavertail and hold it there.
The Specialist ships with two 8-round magazines with bump pads (10 rounds in 9mm) and is available in either a matte stainless finish or our Duty Black finish, which makes for an especially hardy pistol that scoffs at everyday wear and tear.
